N2  - This note integrates the models of Dewan and Mendelson (1998) (DM) and Kyle (1985), extending the DM analysis of time-based competition in financial markets to the case of endogenous liquidity. The results enable us to examine the link between information technology investments, trading strategies, and liquidity.
AB  - This note integrates the models of Dewan and Mendelson (1998) (DM) and Kyle (1985), extending the DM analysis of time-based competition in financial markets to the case of endogenous liquidity. The results enable us to examine the link between information technology investments, trading strategies, and liquidity.
